---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About" backgroundColor="#0f0f0d">
    <main class="about-container">
        <a href="/" class="back-link">
            <span class="arrow">←</span>
            <span>take me home</span>
        </a>
        <div class="about-content">
            <h1>Self-taught Developer | Finance Student</h1>
            <p>
                I am a 23-year-old finance and semi-CS student and self-taught
                developer, learning by building, breaking, and iterating. I
                enjoy simple and clean but blazingly fast design. Always had a
                systems thinking wanting to optimize to the last nanosecond. I
                believe in understanding the whole picture in small and scaling
                up from there. Once I finish my BSc I'll be doing a masters in
                Quantitative Finance. I have been obsessed with CLI tools for a
                long time — exploring new technologies, stripping away
                unnecessary bloat, and focusing on mastering the basics. I am
                constantly refining my workflow through automation, scripting,
                and well-structured pipelines that remove friction and make
                ideas easier to test. I specialize in Python, primarily building
                backtesting systems for all kinds of trading strategies. My main
                interest lies in quantitative research, systematic trading, and
                turning financial theory into code that can be tested, measured,
                and broken. I am currently learning C++, with a focus on
                performance, low-level control, and writing faster research
                tooling. I enjoy tinkering with my setup, often breaking things
                I probably should not. NixOS makes that survivable. Over time
                this has turned into a habit of overconfiguring, experimenting,
                and rebuilding until the system feels intentional. This site is
                my workspace made public — small experiments, side projects,
                notes, and ideas that reflect what I am currently curious about.
            </p>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
<style>
    .about-container {
        min-height: 100vh;
        padding: 4rem 2rem;
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        color: #c5c9c5;
    }
    .back-link {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        color: #727169;
        font-size: 1rem;
        text-decoration: none;
        transition: all 0.2s;
        margin-bottom: 3rem;
        font-family: "Fira Code", monospace;
    }
    .back-link:hover {
        color: #9c8d7e;
        transform: translateX(-4px);
    }
    .about-content {
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        align-items: center;
    }
    .about-content h1 {
        font-size: 2.2rem;
        color: #9c8d7e;
        margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
        line-height: 1.3;
        text-align: center;
    }
    .about-content p {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 1.15rem;
        line-height: 1.8;
        color: #c5c9c5;
        letter-spacing: 0.015em;
    }
    .internal-link {
        color: #c5c9c5;
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-decoration-style: dashed;
        text-underline-offset: 6px;
        transition: color 0.2s;
    }
    .internal-link:hover {
        color: #ec753a;
        cursor: help;
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
        .about-container {
            padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
        }
        .about-content h1 {
            white-space: normal;
        }
    }
</style>
